<p>
  <strong>Couple Joy</strong> turns daily questions into a game and leans hard into long-distance features — distance widgets, disappearing Stories, real-time mood. <strong>OurCouple</strong> is an all-in-one private space built around daily rituals, memories and games. Here's the honest comparison.
</p>

<h2>The Short Version</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Couple Joy</strong> is a long-distance-friendly questions app: 3000+ daily emotional prompts, home-screen widgets (distance between you, countdown to your next visit), real-time mood sharing, 24-hour Stories, and a shared photo journal. The free tier limits questions; <strong>$29.99/year</strong> unlocks everything.</li>
  <li><strong>OurCouple</strong> is an all-in-one private space built around a <strong>living couple card</strong>: a daily ritual (a question, a photo, a message), daily questions, a shared memory journal, love notes, a calendar, couple games with a <strong>compatibility score</strong>, and a virtual pet you raise together — end-to-end encrypted, with a 7-day free trial and one plan for both partners.</li>
</ul>

<p>
  <strong>Short answer:</strong> if you want a huge daily-question bank, real-time mood and disappearing Stories, Couple Joy delivers. If you want one private space for rituals, memories and games — long-distance widgets included — with a compatibility score that grows over time, OurCouple fits better.
</p>

